  "title": "Account & Sale Support Manager | Full Sets | 5 Days | SS10",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: Account and Sale Support Manager</strong></p><p><strong>Industry: Development Business</strong></p><p><strong>Location: Jalan Besar</strong></p><p><strong>5 days | Mon to Thur [ 930am – 630pm | Fri [ 930am – 530pm]</strong></p><p><strong>Salary: $4000 - $5500 [Depends on experience]</strong></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Diploma/Degree in Accounting, Finance, Business, or related field.</strong></li><li><strong>Prefer experience with Account / Audit firm</strong></li><li><strong>At least 3–5 years of relevant experience in accounting, tax, or corporate secretarial roles.</strong></li><li><strong>Experience in managing or supervising a team is preferred.</strong></li><li><strong>Strong knowledge of Singapore accounting standards, GST requirements, and corporate tax regulations.</strong></li><li><strong>Familiarity with cloud accounting software such as Xero is an advantage.</strong></li></ol><p><br /><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>We are looking for a dedicated and experienced Accounts & Sales Support Manager to lead our accounting and tax team while supporting the operations of our sales division. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in accounting, tax, and corporate secretarial work, with excellent leadership and client management skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Leadership & Management</p><ul><li>Lead and manage a team of accounting and tax executives, providing guidance, training, and performance management.</li><li>Oversee daily operations of the accounting and tax department to ensure tasks are completed accurately, efficiently and within filing due dates.</li></ul><p>Accounting & Tax Review</p><ul><li>Review full sets of accounts and GST reports prepared by accounts executives.</li><li>Review unaudited financial statements and corporate tax computations prepared by tax executives.</li><li>Ensure all client deliverables and statutory deadlines are met consistently.</li></ul><p>Client Relationship Management</p><ul><li>Maintain a professional and positive working relationship with clients.</li><li>Provide timely support, address queries, and ensure high client satisfaction.</li></ul><p>Sales Support</p><ul><li>Support the sales team in daily and ongoing operations, including documentation, client onboarding, grant application support, follow-ups on meeting deadlines, and coordination.</li><li>Assist in preparing quotations, billings and communicating service deliverables to clients.</li></ul><p>Samuel Siaw</p><p>The Supreme HR Advisory Pte Ltd</p><p>EA No: 14C7279</p><p>Reg No: R2412474</p><p></p>",
